description.narrative: The political transition, the;second year of the pandemic and the new influx of Afghan Refugees;slowed down implementation of regular activities. In this volatile;context, UNICEF re-prioritized;activities and resources to respond to;emergencies;and adjust to;new political setting. UNICEF successfully maintained 14 active workplans and seized the refugee crisis;to engage more directly with affected populations and host communities,;develop new partnership with humanitarian actors. ICO lead the wash, education, nutrition and CP sectors and;successfully;mobilized emergency funds. UNICEF also;revived its partnership with BAFIA and increased access to affected populations in;No Go areas. In addition UNICEF initiated fruitfull;negocitiation with the new administration for the new CPD. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/01/2022
